The biggest challenges facing the education sector today are:
1) The lack of qualified teachers and trainers, especially in rural areas;
2) The lack of adequate infrastructure (buildings, equipment, etc.) to meet the needs of students;
3) The high cost of education, which makes it difficult for many families to send their children to school;
4) The low quality of education, particularly in primary schools;
5) The lack of support from the government and other stakeholders for the development of the education sector.
